    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-27T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="154"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/334: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-27T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received November 28, 2.10 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Legation’s Nov. 25, 9 a.m. After Chilean disturbances and withdrawal Peruvian
                    consuls, Chile authorized withdrawal her consuls from Peru but most of them have
                    remained. Learned today confidentially that Chilean Consul General will leave.
                    Peruvian authorities have urged people be quiet and abstain from all hostile
                    demonstrations with good results.</p>
                <p>Italian Minister a Lima suggested to his Government propriety admonishing Chile
                    against violence towards Peru.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
